    • Method Detail

      • createOrGetTypedDiscoursePart

        public DiscoursePart createOrGetTypedDiscoursePart(Discourse discourse,
                                                   DiscoursePartTypes type)
        Retrieves existing or creates a new DiscoursePartType entity with the provided type. It then creates a new empty DiscoursePart entity, connects it with the type and the provided discourse.
        All changed/created entities are committed to the db and the DiscoursePart is returned.
        The discoursePartName is constructed like this: discourseName_DiscoursePartType.
        Use createOrGetTypedDiscoursePart(Discourse discourse, String discoursePartName, DiscoursePartTypes type) to explicitly set the discoursePartName.
        Parameters:
        discourse - the discourse of which the new DiscoursePart is a part of
        type - the value for the DiscoursePartType
        Returns:
        a new empty DiscoursePart that is already saved to the db and connected with its requested type

        Parameters:

      • createTypedDiscoursePart

        public DiscoursePart createTypedDiscoursePart(Discourse discourse,
                                              DiscoursePartTypes type)
        Creates a new DiscoursePart with the provided parameters even if a DiscoursePart with the same name already exists. The discoursePartName is constructed like this: discourseName_DiscoursePartType.
        Use createTypedDiscoursePart(Discourse discourse, String discoursePartName, DiscoursePartTypes type) to explicitly set the discoursePartName. If duplicate discoursePartNames should be avoided, use createOrGetTypedDiscoursePart(Discourse discourse, DiscoursePartTypes type). This only creates a DiscoursePart if none with the same name exists and retrieves the existing one otherwise.. Duplicate names make sense if the DiscoursePart is further disambiguated with DataSources or through relations with other DiscourseParts.
        Parameters:
        discourse - the discourse of which the new DiscoursePart is a part of
        type - the value for the DiscoursePartType
        Returns:
        a new empty DiscoursePart that is already saved to the db and connected with its requested type

                                              String discoursePartName,
                                              DiscoursePartTypes type)
        Creates a new DiscoursePart with the provided parameters even if a DiscoursePart with the same name already exists. If duplicate discoursePartNames should be avoided, use createOrGetTypedDiscoursePart(Discourse discourse, String discoursePartName, DiscoursePartTypes type). This only creates a DiscoursePart if none with the same name exists and retrieves the existing one otherwise.. Duplicate names make sense if the DiscoursePart is further disambiguated with DataSources or through relations with other DiscourseParts.
        Parameters:

      • addContributionToDiscoursePart

        public DiscoursePartContribution addContributionToDiscoursePart(Contribution contrib,
                                                                DiscoursePart dPArt)
        Adds the given contribution to the provided DiscoursePart. The start date of the relation between the two is initialized with the creation date of the contribution. In case this is not true, the DiscoursePartContribution relation has to be created manually or updated accordingly.
        Parameters:
        contrib - the contribution that is part of the given DiscoursePart.
        dPArt - the DiscoursePart that contains the given contribution.

      • createDiscoursePartRelation

        public DiscoursePartRelation createDiscoursePartRelation(DiscoursePart sourceDiscoursePart,
                                                         DiscoursePart targetDiscoursePart,
                                                         DiscoursePartRelationTypes type)
        Creates a new DiscoursePartRelation of the given type between the two provided DiscourseParts. Depending on the type, the relation might be directed or not. This information should be given in the type definition. If a DiscoursePartRelation of the given type already exists between the two DiscourseParts (taking into account the direction of the relation), then the existing relation is returned. DiscourseDB does not enforce the uniqueness of these relations by default, but enforcing it in this service method will cater to most of the use cases we will see.
        Parameters:
        sourceDiscoursePart - the source or parent DiscoursePart of the relation
        targetDiscoursePart - the target or child DiscoursePart of the relation
        type - the DiscoursePartRelationTypes
        Returns:
        a DiscoursePartRelation between the two provided DiscourseParts with the given type that has already been saved to the database
